## Section 1 — The Cannon Hall

IMG-01-01: Long stone cannon hall, arches receding into shadow, bronze and iron cannon on trestles along both walls, grey light from open door and high windows, dust motes, scribe at entrance with register, guard with torch behind, cool grey and amber bronze
IMG-01-02: Close mid-shot of small bronze cannon on low trestles, scribe's hands with register and quill marking count, torchlight from right, barrels gleaming dully, one trestle empty with bolt still in frame, warm amber and cool bronze
IMG-01-03: Long-barrelled bronze cannon on trestles from the side, barrels extending beyond supports, scribe with register from far end, stone wall behind, torch on bracket casting amber pool, cool grey and amber bronze
IMG-01-04: Wide cannon hall interior, dense ordnance rows, bronze and iron colubrine on trestles receding into shadow, stone arches above, small scribe mid-distance between rows, cold window light, cool grey stone and bronze amber
IMG-01-05: Far end of stone cannon hall in darkness, single torch held, short heavy iron bombards on trestles against rear wall, thick muzzles facing viewer, moisture on wall, scribe and guard as foreground silhouettes, amber torch glow, deep shadow
IMG-01-06: Close shot of thick iron cannon on trestle, scribe holding bronze calibre gauge against the bore, lamplight from left on barrel and gauge, register on trestle beside, bore in shadow, warm amber and dark iron
IMG-01-07: Close overhead of open register on rough table, cannon entry in clerical hand, second hand writing marginal note in different ink, quill mid-stroke, inkwell nearby, second register for cross-reference, torchlight upper left, parchment and amber ink
IMG-01-08: Wooden storage bins along cannon hall north wall, painted number labels, several lids open showing cannonballs of different sizes, scribe counting at an open bin from behind, guard with lamp nearby, warm amber and cool grey stone
IMG-01-09: Cannon hall door pulled closed at dusk, last amber sky through narrowing gap, guard silhouette in doorway, scribe with register under arm walking toward door, cannon rows fading to shadow, dusk light against interior darkness
IMG-01-10: Small dark stone room off cannon hall, lit by held torch, shelves with cowhide powder flasks and iron ladles on poles, bronze calibre gauges on cord from hook, scribe crouching examining a gauge, warm amber torch against dark stone
IMG-01-11: Scribe pressing bronze calibre gauge to large iron cannon bore, second gauge set on trestle, two registers cross-referenced on nearby surface, focused expression, torch from behind in sharp relief, warm amber and dark iron tones

