## Section 2 — Rope, Sail, and Timber

IMG-02-01: Vast stone-vaulted rope factory receding into darkness, great hemp coils on iron hooks along both walls, floor dusted with pale fibre, scribe and foreman tiny in foreground against the scale, cool grey stone and warm amber coil tones
IMG-02-02: Close shot of massive hemp rope coils on iron wall hooks, each with cord and wooden tag, one hook with only blank cord where tag is missing, scribe's hand holding tag to lamplight, warm amber and earthy hemp brown
IMG-02-03: Rope factory wall with neat rows of progressively lighter coils each tagged, grey light from high clerestory opposite, scribe with ledger counting along the wall, Tana foreman in apron behind, grey-green ambient light
IMG-02-04: Rope-factory wall with hanging coils, one hook visibly empty with no coil no tag no cord, scribe pointing to empty hook while foreman checks ledger, surrounding coils undisturbed, cool interior light
IMG-02-05: Eastern end of rope factory less orderly, reserve coils piled on stone floor not on hooks, hooks missing where plaster fell, raw brick through collapsed cladding, scribe and foreman among floor stacks, darker cooler tone
IMG-02-06: Corner of rope factory, forty stacked coils against wall near door, no hooks or tags, texture differs from registered stock, board with faint writing against stack, scribe writing in register, foreman beside, muted tones
IMG-02-07: Arsenal yard with covered timber sheds, four tile-roofed structures in row, planking on trestles under lean-to, cold November sky, wet ground, scribe with register and foreman walking between sheds, muted ochre and grey
IMG-02-08: Timber shed packed with stacked raw oak on supports, pale recent wood versus darker seasoned stock, scribe measuring space with cord, shed overfull, equally packed stack through open doorway, warm pale wood in cool grey light
IMG-02-09: Arsenal timber yard outdoors, heavy oak beams under tarpaulins on supports, two tarps split along seams exposing timber, water stains on beam faces, scribe and foreman inspecting split cover, grey November sky, muddy ground, grey and ochre
IMG-02-10: Far eastern timber yard, scattered deteriorated planks on low supports, yellow paint strips on each, several warped or rotted, no tarp remaining, scribe counting while foreman holds ledger, cold light, arsenal wall behind, dark wood and grey-green
IMG-02-11: Small lockable room by the rope factory, shelves with folded oilcloth packages marked with sail type and dimensions, scribe counting on shelf, Tana foreman with keys and ledger, grey light from one window, cool grey and pale cream

