## Section 3 — Galley Shed Assessment

IMG-03-01: Large galley shed exterior, heavy wooden doors on stone arch, scribe in dark robes with satchel and register beside master carpenter in apron with mallet and ledger, doors barely open, cold grey morning, muted grey and dark wood
IMG-03-02: Galley shed interior, long wooden hull on support blocks with clean intact lines, scribe along port side noting, proto following, hull dwarfing both figures, water through half-open gate, cold grey light, dark wood and grey stone
IMG-03-03: Beneath galley hull in shed, proto crouching under keel with torch examining damage, scribe kneeling with open register, keel showing longitudinal crack, hull underside filling frame, warm torch amber and dark timber shadow
IMG-03-04: Wide galley shed, three hulls on blocks at different depths, proto and scribe small beside middle hull, name boards on each bow, timber trusses overhead, gate open at far end with grey daylight, dark muted palette
IMG-03-05: Deteriorated galley hull on blocks, keel line broken, strake planking fallen inward, bow leaning off true, scribe writing lengthy entry, proto standing back arms folded, darker muted palette with hull in shadow
IMG-03-06: Very old galley hull filling shed centre, darkened flaking wood, bow name board faded near-illegible, scribe copying remains of the name, proto standing aside, very dark wood and grey stone with muted warm timber tones
IMG-03-07: Close shot of galley midship planking, bolted timber patch with lead sheeting on port side, discolored but intact, scribe pointing to patch while holding register with no entry for it, warm torch amber, timber and lead tones
IMG-03-08: Small workspace in galley shed corner, rough table with open register and spring register, scribe writing closing certification by lamplight, hulls in soft focus through doorway behind, warm amber lamp and cool grey shed
IMG-03-09: Small workroom, framed proto's manual on stone wall, carpenter and scribe before it, carpenter pointing to a provision, scribe with register for comparison, table with notes nearby, lamplight from left, warm amber and grey-brown
IMG-03-10: Galley shed filled with deteriorated hulls, five on blocks with darkened flaking wood, nearest hull deck rotted at bow, shed dark and still, proto outside entrance looking in, scribe noting beside him, deep shadow and aged timber

