## Section 4 — Oars, Anchors, and the Cyprus Loan

IMG-04-01: Large oar storage shed, parallel racks full length holding bundled oars in stacked tiers receding into shadow, oars stored horizontally, scribe and assistant small near first rack, cool grey wood and pale fir tones
IMG-04-02: Scribe and young assistant counting oars from opposite rack sides, each with tally booklet marking counts, scribe calling number across, oar bundles filling the frame, warm grey-brown timber
IMG-04-03: Wide empty oar rack in shed, pegs present but no oars, identification board at end visible, adjacent rack fully loaded at frame edge, scribe before the empty rack staring, foreman behind, cool grey shadow with visual absence
IMG-04-04: Close overhead of open document box on rough table, folded documents within, one unfolded held by scribe showing formal layout with seal impression, inkwell and quill aside, register beside, amber lamplight, parchment cream and amber
IMG-04-05: Inventory register page, rack seventeen entry with cross-reference in different hand, later marginal annotation, entry distinct from clean surrounding entries, scribe's finger on the marginal note, parchment and ink tones
IMG-04-06: Outdoor platform under lean-to in arsenal yard, wooden cradles with iron anchors of varying size, kedge anchors numerous on one side, bower anchors larger and spaced, scribe noting numbers on rings, November light, iron grey and ochre
IMG-04-07: Very large sheet anchor on cradle dwarfing the scribe beside it, ring stamped with catalogue number, smaller bower anchor behind for scale, scribe writing in register, Bucintoro shed in soft background, dark iron and cool grey
IMG-04-08: Three medium iron anchors on cradles in arsenal yard, scribe comparing ledger against stamped ring, foreman pointing and explaining, larger bower anchor behind for scale, cold November light, iron grey and ochre stone
IMG-04-09: Oar shed interior, scribe and assistant on opposite sides of long rack with tally booklets, oar bundles forming dense pale wood wall between them, rack receding in perspective toward far end, warm grey-brown timber

