## Section 5 — Arms, Armour, and Final Certification

IMG-05-01: Stone-vaulted armoury, barrel ceiling, crossbow racks west wall, plate armour on stands south, shield rack north, keeper in apron at door with keys and ledger, scribe entering and surveying, central lamp warm amber, cool grey stone
IMG-05-02: Stone wall with crossbow racks, scribe counting along a rack with finger, keeper with open ledger beside, one position empty with peg present, bows in order, cool grey and dark steel-blue
IMG-05-03: Armoury wall with pavise shields stacked four-deep, several with faded lion-of-Saint-Mark paint, two overpainted white, scribe counting by touching stacks, keeper at doorway, faded reds and golds on aged wood
IMG-05-04: Armoury east wall, iron rods with mail coats in groups of ten, one rod holding eleven with card reading eleven, empty spaces for five in repair, scribe writing annotation, keeper with ledger beside, iron grey and warm amber
IMG-05-05: Table in scribes' room, register open to certification page, scribe finishing signature, two witnesses with quills across table, fourth figure about to sit, thick filled register, inkwell and wax candle, warm amber and parchment
IMG-05-06: Armoury rack shelving behind divider, sword pairs strapped on upper shelf, boarding axes middle, pikes upright against wall, keeper counting swords, scribe behind with register, warm amber light, dark steel and brown leather
IMG-05-07: Close overhead of register on table, scribe's finger down column checking arithmetic, second page showing inventory total beside mobilization figure, inkwell and quill aside, amber lamplight from left, parchment and dark ink

